---
hideHeader: false
layout:  templates/base.html
title: Robert James Gabriel - Software Engineer
youtubeId: PfILiWebkuc
cardTitle: Robert James' Blog
description: Blog posts about tech, accessibility, and whatever else I'm thinking about.
keywords: html5, css3, sass, less, nodejs, vue.js, php, npm, jquery, javascript, angularjs, pwa, data structures, mobile application, golang, helperbird, opendyslexic

url:
---

<div class="px-4 sm:px-8 mt-16">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl lg:max-w-3xl">

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-16">
      <div class="accent-line w-full mb-10"></div>
      <h1 class="text-section text-base-content">Writing</h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-base-content/70">
        Thoughts, discoveries, and technical writeups.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Posts -->
    <div>
      {%- for post in collections.blog reversed -%}
      <article>
        <a href="{{ post.url }}" class="block py-10 border-t border-base-300/50 group" title="{{ post.data.cardTitle }} - Read post" aria-label="{{ post.data.cardTitle }} - Read post">

          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-base-content leading-snug mb-3 group-hover:text-primary transition-colors duration-200">
            {{ post.data.cardTitle }}
          </h2>

          {% if post.data.blog_snip %}
          <p class="text-base text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed mb-4 max-w-xl">
            {{ post.data.blog_snip }}
          </p>
          {% endif %}

          <time datetime="{{ post.data.dated }}" class="text-sm text-base-content/50">
            {{ post.data.dated }}
          </time>
        </a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor -%}
      <div class="border-t border-base-300/50"></div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>
